'''Background Draw a Secret''' (BDAS), a variant of [[Draw a Secret]], is purely graphical password selection and input scheme.
The scheme replaces alphanumeric password strings, with a simple picture drawn on a background image. <ref>[http://www.ncl.ac.uk/press.office/newslink/?ref=1193216061 Newcastle University NewsLink, October 24 2007]</ref>

